@node Main "VLT Help"

   @{" COPYRIGHT " link COPYRIGHT}  @{" DISCLAIMER " link DISCLAIMER}  @{" AUTHOR " link AUTHOR}


   VLT Documentation
   -----------------

   This guide does not cover all aspects of VLT - it is mainly intended as
   an on-line help system.

   @{" Changes since v.5.576    " link CHANGES_5576}
   @{" Changes before v.5.576   " link vlt5p576.doc/main}

   @{" PingServer Documentation " link PINGSERVER}

   More detailed documentation is contained in the

   @{" VLT Printed Manual       " link MANUAL}

   which is available at no cost from Stanford Linear Accelerator Center.


   VLT Menus
   ---------

   VLT has two main subsystems, the VT100 (main) window, and the Graphics
   (Tektronix) window. The Main window includes a Session History window.
   All three of these have separate menus:

   @{" Main Menus               " link VLT_MMENUS}
   @{" Session History Menus    " link VLT_HMENUS}
   @{" Graphics Menus           " link VLT_GMENUS}

   VLTjr does not have a Graphics subsystem.


   VLT Commands
   ------------

   VLT has an extensive scripting language, usable in native scripts and
   from ARexx.

   @{" Script Language Overview " link VLT_SCRIPT}
   @{" Script Command Reference " link cmds_alpha}
@endnode

